HEADWORD: Plebicolist
<hw>Ple*bic"o*list</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>plebs</ets> the common people + <ets>colere</ets> to
cultivate.]</ety> <def>One who flatters, or courts the favor of, the
common people; a demagogue.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

